cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the separation of control and forwarding planes in networking and evaluates the traffic between these two planes. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on content distribution and content-oriented network architectures, which are related to distributed computing. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses content routing and content discovery, which are relevant to information networks. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to the control plane and forwarding plane interface. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may discuss algorithms for minimizing the cost of overhead in maintaining the location of content in the control plane.
